<br>
Not to be a wet blanket, but an IP address is all somebody needs to know if they wish to do serious harm to your computer.  That is the starting point at which all internet communications take place.<br>
<br>
What most servers do (and services) is have you link to them, and then THEY send information to and from everyone on the network, so no direct connection to anyone is ever established, and your identity is safe.  I personally use a multi-proxy to mask where I am, except in the case of EZBoard. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:perpetua;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=421973">Turzem Setanta</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->--<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower">Arch Mage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nanamarinfernostorm>Nanamar Infernostorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 531<br> <font color=#333333>(11/18/02 1:55:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7894.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HMmmm...</span><hr size=1> Yeah I have a linksys router as my firewall and I often keep the Internet Connection Firewall in XP up, oh well what can I do? <p>Master Nanamar Infernostorm<br>
